            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#_a"><name nymRef="#_α"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><seg part="F">α</seg></name></persName> <g type="punct">:</g> 
                        <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><expan><abbr>Ἀπόλλ</abbr><ex>ων</ex></expan></name></persName> <g type="punct">:</g>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem><expan><abbr>Ἀπόλλ</abbr><ex>ων</ex></expan></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#ferri1923">Ἀπόλλ<supplied reason="lost">ωνος</supplied></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><expan><abbr>Ἀπόλλ</abbr><ex>ωνος</ex></expan></rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>a. <expan><abbr>Apoll</abbr><ex>on</ex></expan>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>a. <expan><abbr>Apoll</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>a. <expan><abbr>Apoll</abbr><ex>o</ex></expan>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This belongs to the series of altars with compartments of the so-called '<foreign xml:lang="it">agorà degli dei</foreign>'.</p>
                <p>One name should have been inscribed in correspondence with each compartment.</p>
	            <p>The name on the left was probably that of a feminin deity; thus Apollo's name, here abbreviated, should also be expanded at the nominative.</p>
                <p>Alternatively, the first name might be that of a rare masculine in -<foreign xml:lang="grc">ας</foreign>, such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀρχαγέτας</foreign>, 
                    and we should thus read <foreign xml:lang="grc"><expan><abbr>Ἀπόλλ</abbr><ex>ωνος</ex></expan></foreign>. However this hypotheses seems to be less 
                probable.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
